upt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> Hey guys i've tried a couple of times ot get this guy but i keep getting swamped by adds and having to gate out.  Anyone got any suggestions as to a safe or farely safe place to pull to to make this guy pop?<br>
<br>
Wenamwen Morson<br>
Wanderer of the 51st season<br>
Druzel Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urheawindsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhea Windsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 11:47:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> pull them to the FoB zone. I brought a bard along with me and it went much faster. <p><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/Rhea69/RHEATAG2.JPG></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelawnah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elawnah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.planetunreal.com/images/mgwhore.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 5:23:10 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.artexpressions.net/esm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> go to the FoB zone as they suggested... and fear kite. Helps to have a melee class along with ya. (i love it that this gorilla counts as an animal.) <p>Always sexy,<BR>
<A HREF= http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=61157> Elawnah Mousebane</A><BR>
52nd level Wanderer, Officer in <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/btroublesband>Trouble's Band</A><BR>
Rodcet Nife


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushanarwolfinator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShanarWolfinator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 5:34:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> Fight on the Plateau, you dont get that many adds, and thats where 3 of the PH tottering gorilla's spawn, i usually got 1 tainted to spawn every 20 or 30 minutes, i casted Winged Death and my arms, and  then arms again and they died, its not hard to take up to 5 things root/dot at once just using your arms, just a pain =) i never had to do it, i sat at a wall and pulled them to there, a few things roamed by, but nothing that i couldn't avoid. It took 7 tainted to finally get the corrupted, but it only took me about 4-5 hours. And at 56 i still got exp on some of the tottering gorillas, and the tainted/corrupted both conned blue(the real tainted that is) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uicknay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Icknay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 5:57:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> I soloed the monkey at 51.  Was very hard and quite time consuming.  Pull him near the fob zone and keep him snared and rooted.  Unsnared he is very dangerous.  If you're alone just deal with the adds.  I think I had 3 that I had to root/dot whilst dealing with him...kept running outta mana but eventually I got him. <br>
Icknay<br>
54th Druid<br>
Blood and Honor<br>
Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=akanaetendo>Akanae Tendo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 6:42:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> if you pull to the wall on the far north/west part of the Plateau, there are a couple places there where you won't get adds (I was behind a row of pillars...). I dont suggest pulling every tottering to FoB zone, just because its a long pull ...makes more chances for adds, and its a pain in the butt to pull a million gorrilas that far. Once the live tainted popd for me I pulled him to FoB zone, and just kept him rooted/dot'd, same with corrupted. Both went down fairly easy for me at lvl 52.<br>
<br>
Akanae Tendo lvl 52 Druid<br>
Aawy Meatshield lvl 29 warrior<br>
officer- Un-Natural Selection<br>
Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=caraddor>Caraddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 5:00:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> I originally started trying this to get the gorilla down on the forest floor.  I spent a few hours pulling to the north wall near the cliff, and never really had a problem with adds there.  After a while, I moved up to the plains area in the northwest corner.  There is a row of pillars there, and a ruins type building.  I found that there were very few wanderers in that area (was hanging out between the building and the zone wall).  Pulling was a cinch (invis, track a tottering/tainted, snare/flame lick depending on length of pull, reinvis, run back to camp).  Never had an add.  I had my brother bring his 52 retired druid out to help just in case, but in retrospect I don't think I needed him to be there.  Was nice to have some company though.<br>
<br>
Good luck on the gorilla and the rest of your epic.<br>
<br>
Caraddor (Order of the Scattered Winds)<br>
52 Wanderer<br>
Bertoxx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyungodarkthorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yungodarkthorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 10:03:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question on the Corrupt Gorrila</span><hr size=1> The first time I went looking for this guy Severilous was up so I said the hell with it. So then a few days ago I went back and found a tainted on the plateau, killed it, and the corrupted spawn. It took me all of about 5 minutes, hehe. Don't hate me! :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4699.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4691.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.emailToFriend?topicID=4701.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.threadControl?topicID=4701.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4701.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4701.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right">